Add reset diagnostics so we can see if the fix is actually live (v0.1.91)

User reports v0.1.90 reset still produces the warped 192742-style
output instead of the clean 192858 baseline. Most likely cause:
GitHub Pages cached the old HTML and the browser hasn't fetched
the new build yet. Adds two console.log lines so devtools can
confirm whether the v0.1.90+ code path is actually executing:

  [ai-calibration-reset] v0.1.90 reset starting -- N display(s)
  ... (per surviving warpMesh)
  [ai-calibration-reset] cleaned N -- 0 survivors w/ _isCustom=true

If the user sees nothing in console after clicking Reset, they
are on a cached older build -- hard-refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R)
should pull v0.1.91 and the reset will null warpMesh as designed.

If the user sees survivors > 0 with _isCustom=true, that means
the warp meshes are flagged as user-edits and the reset is
skipping them by design; we'll need a separate "force reset"
flag for that case.

